1382","about 1355":"omkring 1355","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom","Lapworth, Warwickshire, England":"Lapworth, Warwickshire, England"},"nl":{"Abt 1356–":"circa 1356–Overleden","1356–Male":"1356–Overleden","1360–Female":"1360–Overleden","1380–1468":"1380–1468","1332–1389":"1332–1389","1335–Female":"1335–Overleden","1468":"1468","1335":"1335","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1332":"1332","Abt 1356":"circa 1356","1382":"1382","about 1355":"circa 1355","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Lapworth, Warwickshire, England":"Lapworth, Warwickshire, England"},"en":{"Abt 1356–":"about 1356–Deceased","1356–Male":"1356–Deceased","1360–Female":"1360–Deceased","1380–1468":"1380–1468","1332–1389":"1332–1389","1335–Female":"1335–Deceased","1468":"1468","1335":"1335","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1332":"1332","Abt 1356":"about 1356","1382":"1382","about 1355":"about 1355","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom","Lapworth, Warwickshire, England":"Lapworth, Warwickshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Brome","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English, Scottish:  see  Broom  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Broom","meanings":["English: variant of   Broome  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":26,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705197,"age":99,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Brome III was born about 1356, in Warwickshire, England, his father, Robert de Brome II, was 26 and his mother, Margery Brooke, was 22. He married Matilda Stanley in 1382, in Warwickshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1356–":"umbes 1356–Surnud","1356–Male":"1356–Surnud","1360–Female":"1360–Surnud","1380–1468":"1380–1468","1332–1389":"1332–1389","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","1468":"1468","1335":"1335","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1332":"1332","Abt 1356":"umbes 1356","1382":"1382","about 1355":"umbes 1355","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lapworth, Warwickshire, England":"Lapworth, Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1356–":"noin 1356–Kuollut","1356–Male":"1356–Kuollut","1360–Female":"1360–Kuollut","1380–1468":"1380–1468","1332–1389":"1332–1389","1335–Female":"1335–Kuollut","1468":"1468","1335":"1335","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1332":"1332","Abt 1356":"noin 1356","1382":"1382","about 1355":"noin 1355","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lapworth, Warwickshire, England":"Lapworth, Warwickshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1356–":"environ 1356–Décédé","1356–Male":"1356–Décédé","1360–Female":"1360–Décédée","1380–1468":"1380–1468","1332–1389":"1332–1389","1335–Female":"1335–Décédée","1468":"1468","1335":"1335","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1332":"1332","Abt 1356":"environ 1356","1382":"1382","about 1355":"environ 1355","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Lapworth, Warwickshire, England":"Lapworth, Warwickshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert de Brome III est né environ 1356, à War